  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nScope of the issue is to toggle toolbar visibility in the browser. Once you scroll down, they should animate and hide away, and if you scroll up, they reappear. It's a pattern common in mobile browsers.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to have a more immersive experience when browsing the web, hiding any UI chrome when it's not needed and giving me the most of screen real estate.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nA scroll down with sufficient enough velocity should toggle toolbars to hide, and inversely a scroll up to have them appear again.\r\n\r\n[The full extent of what I mean by toolbars is visible in this Figma here](https://www.figma.com/file/MYWmd1buvc2AMvUmFP9w42t5/Browser?node-id=4237%3A587)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"600\" alt=\"Scroll\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/127474691-4cabcc33-d935-488d-a6b2-58ffe80fdf64.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nProper behaviour, animation, velocity were implemented. Toolbars act as you'd expect them to (when in doubt reference Mobile Safari)\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n",
